285 g Top Sirloin Steak
227 g Broccoli
2 tbsp Soy Sauce
0.13 cup Vegetarian Oyster Sauce
2 unit(s) Green Onion
3 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
200 g Ramen Noodles
56 g Carrot, julienned
2 tbsp Spicy Mayo
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
½ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Peel, then grate or mince garlic.
Thinly slice green onions.
Add soy sauce, oyster sauce, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water to a small bowl, then whisk to combine. Set aside.

Pat steaks dry with paper towels, then season with salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add half the sesame oil, then steaks. Sear until golden-brown,1-2 per side.
Transfer steaks to an unlined baking sheet. Roast in the middle of the oven until cooked to desired doneness, 5-8 min.**

Meanwhile, add broccoli and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water to the same pan (used in step 2).
Cook, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is tender-crisp and water has evaporated, 3-5 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Add garlic, carrots and remaining sesame oil. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant and carrots are tender, 1-2 min.

While broccoli cooks, add ramen noodles to the boiling water. Cook uncovered until tender, 1-2 min.
Drain noodles, then rinse under warm water.

Add ramen and soy-oyster mixture to the pan. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly, 1-2 min.
Remove the pan with heat, then season with pepper.

Thinly slice steak.
Divide ramen between bowls.
Top with steak.
Drizzle spicy mayo over top.
Sprinkle green onions over top.